COPYRIGHT 2006, 2007, 2008 BLUE CROSS/BLUE SHIELD OF KANSAS CITY 
                           

PROCESSING:  This job is called multiple times with a different CommitCnt value.  The CommitCnt value deteremines which batch of records to extract from the W_CLM_INIT table.  Those records are written to the CLM_DM_INIT_CLM table in the Claim Datamart.  The CLM_DM_INIT_CLM table has so many indexes that row updates occur at 5 rows a second.  By looping through the data, restarts after an abort don't have to process records already updated.  DBA suggested multiple updates can occur similtainioiusly so 3 more updates were added.  If no rows exist for CommitCnt SQL does not complain.


MODIFICATIONS:
